34,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.58,\n      \"feedback\": \"Formate is a strong hydrothermal hub in the literature, but this pathway appears to imply formate-to-CO progression without an explicit reaction implementing that conversion. As a named pathway it therefore lacks internal graph support, even though its constituent hydrothermal steps are individually plausible. The final acetyl-CoA claim remains unsupported.\",\n      \"approved\": false,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [\n        \"rxn_002\",\n        \"rxn_003\",\n        \"rxn_014\"\n      ],\n      \"suggestions\": [\n        \"Add an explicit formate-to-CO or formate-to-methyl-branch reaction if this convergence is intended\",\n        \"Avoid pathway descriptions that rely on nonexistent edges in the graph\",\n        \"Keep formate as a hub but show its downstream utilization explicitly\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P8\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\n        \"rxn_009\": 0.98,\n        \"rxn_013\": 0.36,\n        \"rxn_014\": 0.28\n      },\n      \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.45,\n      \"pathway_coherence\": 0.5,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.7,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.25,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.43,\n      \"feedback\": \"This pathway is the weakest among the pantetheine-related routes. Reaction 13 is chemically and conceptually problematic because methyl thioacetate plus cysteamine should produce an acetylated cysteamine thioester or thiol-exchange product, not pantetheine. It conflates cysteamine with pantetheine biosynthesis. The late assembly to full acetyl-CoA is also unsupported.\",\n      \"approved\": false,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [\n        \"rxn_013\",\n        \"rxn_014\"\n      ],\n      \"suggestions\": [\n        \"Separate pantetheine synthesis from thioester transfer chemistry\",\n        \"Use cysteamine as a thiol acceptor to form acetyl-cysteamine, not pantetheine\",\n        \"If pantetheine is desired, derive it 