hotochemistry", "aqueous": "true", "other": "anoxic surface pool; disulfide-based sulfur donor required; no external oxidant"}, "mechanism": "Pyruvate undergoes UV-driven oxidative decarboxylation in the presence of disulfides to yield activated thioacetate esters.", "reasoning": "Leqraa et al. (2020) demonstrated that pyruvate reacts with disulfides under UV irradiation to form thioacetate esters without an external oxidant. The network uses dimethyl disulfide as the sulfur-state-correct precursor to S-methyl thioacetate, correcting earlier over-simplification."}, {"id": "rxn_011", "name": "Thioester-phosphate exchange from S-methyl thioacetate to acetyl phosphate", "inputs": ["mol_012"], "outputs": ["mol_013"], "environment": "Biochemical", "agents": ["null", "null"], "conditions": {"temperature": "298-323K", "pressure": "1 atm", "catalyst": "null", "aqueous": "true", "other": "requires inorganic phosphate in neutral to mildly alkaline aqueous solution"}, "mechanism": "Nucleophilic phosphate attack on the thioester carbonyl transfers the acetyl group from sulfur to phosphate, generating acetyl phosphate.", "reasoning": "Martin & Russell (2007) emphasized acetyl phosphate as a plausible primordial energy currency formed from acetyl thioesters and inorganic phosphate. The supplied literature explicitly identifies acetyl phosphate as a bridge between thioester and phosphate metabolism."}, {"id": "rxn_012", "name": "Prebiotic synthesis of pantetheine from nitrile-based precursor chemistry", "inputs": ["mol_010"], "outputs": ["mol_014"], "environment": "Surface", "agents": ["phosphate minerals (apatite/struvite)", "borate minerals (colemanite/ulexite)"], "conditions": {"temperature": "298K", "pressure": "1 atm", "catalyst": "mineral-assisted concentration/stabilization", "aqueous": "true", "other": "room-temperature aqueous chemoselective nitrile chemistry; multistep network condensed to preserve connectivity"}, "mechanism": "Nitrile-based aqueous chemistry constructs 