ns well with literature on acetyl-thioester and pantetheine formation, but does not achieve the declared target in a literature-grounded manner. It should be considered a high-quality network for proto-acetyl-CoA chemistry, not an approved network for full acetyl-CoA synthesis.\",\n  \"hub_quality\": 0.88,\n  \"convergence_quality\": 0.86\n}", "parsed_response": {"pathway_evaluations": [{"pathway_id": "P1", "reaction_scores": {"rxn_002": 0.95, "rxn_006": 0.97, "rxn_012": 0.82, "rxn_013": 0.12}, "chemical_feasibility": 0.72, "pathway_coherence": 0.88, "environmental_progression": 0.9, "target_achievement": 0.38, "overall_confidence": 0.72, "feedback": "Strong literature alignment for hydrothermal CO generation and Ni/Fe-sulfide-mediated thioester formation, and a reasonable transfer to pantetheine chemistry. The main weakness is the final conversion from acetyl-pantetheine to full acetyl-CoA, which is explicitly speculative and unsupported by the cited prebiotic literature.", "approved": false, "problematic_reactions": ["rxn_013"], "suggestions": ["Reframe the endpoint as acetyl-pantetheine or S-methyl thioacetate rather than full acetyl-CoA", "If acetyl-CoA must remain the target, include explicit adenylation/phosphorylation subunit assembly steps and mark them as unresolved literature gaps"]}, {"pathway_id": "P2", "reaction_scores": {"rxn_007": 0.96, "rxn_012": 0.82, "rxn_013": 0.12}, "chemical_feasibility": 0.73, "pathway_coherence": 0.89, "environmental_progression": 0.86, "target_achievement": 0.38, "overall_confidence": 0.73, "feedback": "This is one of the best-supported entry routes because the geoelectrochemical NiS-derived thioester synthesis closely matches Kitadai et al. 2021. The route remains chemically coherent up to acetyl-pantetheine, but does not credibly complete the transition to full acetyl-CoA.", "approved": false, "problematic_reactions": ["rxn_013"], "suggestions": ["Keep this as a high-confidence route to prebiotic acetyl thioesters", "Separa